    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/rh-index-comparison-5ops",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Comparison Across Five Operating Points",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/hemolysis-experimental-measurements",
      "description": "The CFD model was exercised at five flow-speed operating conditions (2.0 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3.5 L/min at 2500 RPM, 5.0 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3.5 L/min at 3500 RPM, and 5.0 L/min at 3500 RPM) using the Giersiepen power-law hemolysis submodel with coefficients calibrated to bovine blood. Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were converted to the relative hemolysis index (RH) by normalizing against the predicate device experimental baseline measured in a mock-circulatory loop under identical flow conditions. Across all five operating points, RH ranged from 0.71 to 0.94, satisfying the acceptance criterion of RH < 1 at every condition. The worst-case operating point was identified as 3.5 L/min at 3500 RPM (RH = 0.94), consistent with the high blade-tip velocity and recirculation zone extent observed in the velocity field post-processing. Grid-converged solutions on the 6.8 M cell polyhedral mesh were used for all comparisons; Richardson extrapolation confirmed discretization error below 2.1% for NIH at this operating point. The experimental measurements were obtained by Morrison et al. (2019) using a standardized hemolysis protocol with n = 5 replicates per condition; coefficient of variation was below 8% across all conditions. The structured activity record for the CFD execution campaign, including solver version, boundary condition files, and run logs, is documented in the project technical report TR-2023-CPB-07 and was reviewed by the credibility assessment team prior to acceptance of this result.",
      "outcomeValue": "RH_max = 0.94 at 3.5 L/min / 3500 RPM; all five operating points satisfy RH < 1",
      "passFail": "Pass"
    },
